{{Quote|Banthas, all right.|Luke Skywalker, to C-3PO, not considering that the droid might not be able to distinguish a bantha from a panda|<ref name="ANHn">[[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope'' novelization]]</ref>}}
A '''panda''' was distinct from a [[Bantha/Legends|bantha]],<ref name="ANHn" /> which was a [[Species/Legends|species]] of [[Mammal/Legends|mammals]] [[Homeworld/Legends|native]] to<ref name="Wildlife">''[[The Wildlife of Star Wars: A Field Guide]]''</ref> the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]. In the planet's [[Jundland Wastes/Legends|Jundland Wastes]]<ref name="ANHn" /> in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]],<ref name="Date">''[[X-Wing: The Official Strategy Guide]]'' establishes that the events of [[Star Wars: X-Wing (video game)|''Star Wars: X-Wing'']]{{'s}} third tour of duty take place between the [[Battle of Tatooine (Galactic Civil War)|capture]] of [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] and the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. Both of those events occur in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]] according to ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''. The battle occurs four [[Standard day/Legends|days]] after Organa's capture per the reasoning [[Template:Yavindate|here]], and in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker's]] search for [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] takes place the day after the capture. Since the capture of the [[Priam (starship)|''Priam'']] takes place midway through the third tour of duty, Skywalker's search likely took place before the ''Priam''{{'s}} capture.</ref> as the [[3PO-series protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] accompanied his master&mdash;local [[Moisture farmer/Legends|moisture farmer]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]&mdash;in search of his [[R2-series astromech droid/Legends|astromech droid]], [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]], Skywalker audibly confirmed the presence of several banthas nearby while peering through a pair of [[MB450 macrobinoculars/Legends|macrobinoculars]]. Due to his excitement, he did not consider whether C-3PO could distinguish a bantha from a panda.<ref name="ANHn" />

Soon after in the same [[Standard year/Legends|year]],<ref name="Date" /> the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] deployed a pair of [[Lambda-class T-4a shuttle/Legends|''Lambda''-class T-4a shuttles]] named [[Panda (transports)|''Panda'']] to capture the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] [[EF76 Nebulon-B escort frigate/Legends|frigate]] [[Priam (starship)|''Priam'']].<ref name="X-Wing">[[Star Wars: X-Wing (video game)|''Star Wars: X-Wing'']]</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
A panda was first mentioned in [[Alan Dean Foster]]'s [[1976]] [[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|novelization]]<ref name="ANHn" /> of the [[1977]] [[original trilogy]] film, [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].<ref name="ANH">{{Film|IV}}</ref> It is one of multiple references to [[In-universe|real-world]] wildlife in ''[[Star Wars]]'' media.<ref name="Insider">{{InsiderCite|93|May The Facts Be With You: Part One|May The Facts Be With You: Part One: #1-50}}</ref>

